OpenShadingLanguage
------------------------------------------
Open Shading Language (OSL) is a small but rich language for programmable
shading in advanced renderers and other applications, ideal for describing
materials, lights, displacement, and pattern generation.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.1-1
  libboost_filesystem1.55-1.55.0-2
  libboost_regex1.55-1.55.0-2
  libboost_system1.55-1.55.0-2
  libboost_thread1.55-1.55.0-2
  libboost_wave1.55-1.55.0-2
  libgcc1-4.9.2-3
  libilmbase7-1.0.3-1
  libllvm3.4-3.4.2-5
  libOpenImageIO1.6-1.6.1-1bl1
  libOpenShadingLanguage0-1.6.3dev-1bl1
  libpugixml1-1.5-1bl1
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-1
  bison-3.0.4-1
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/imageworks/OpenShadingLanguage

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/imageworks/OpenShadingLanguage/archive/Release-1.6.3dev.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack OpenShadingLanguage-1.6.3dev-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./OpenShadingLanguage-1.6.3dev-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/OpenShadingLanguage-1.6.3dev-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/OpenShadingLanguage-1.6.3dev-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libOpenShadingLanguage0-1.6.3dev-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libOpenShadingLanguage-devel-1.6.3dev-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

